metadata.name: Diminish
metadata.description:
About Photo: I love this photo because it reminds me how powerful yet so insignificant humans are in this world. This photo is from Jan 2021 when I was on a Himalayan trek. As we were getting ready to move forward for our 3rd stretch of the trek, I saw this beautiful mountain. The peak was shining so good and I instantly got the idea what I wanted to shoot. I asked my friend to pose and I got this shot.

Artist Name: Sachin Chauhan

Edition: 1/1
Size: 3424x4280
Location: Uttarakhand, India
